body:
```mlir
firrtl.circuit "Test" {
  firrtl.module @Test (in %front_port_ahb_0: !firrtl.bundle<hmastlock: uint<1>> [
    {circt.fieldID = 1 : i32, class = "firrtl.transforms.DontTouchAnnotation"},
    {circt.fieldID = 1 : i32, class = "Test"}
  ]) {
 }
}
```
`/bin/circt-opt --firrtl-lower-types ./test.mlir` produces: 
```mlir
module {
  firrtl.circuit "Test"  {
    firrtl.module @Test(in %front_port_ahb_0_hmastlock: !firrtl.uint<1> [{class = "Test"}]) {
    }
  }
}
```
The port should have a symbol on it to indicate `DontTouch`.  If you reverse the order of the annotations, the symbol appears:
```mlir
firrtl.circuit "Test" {
  firrtl.module @Test (in %front_port_ahb_0: !firrtl.bundle<hmastlock: uint<1>> [
    {circt.fieldID = 1 : i32, class = "Test"},
    {circt.fieldID = 1 : i32, class = "firrtl.transforms.DontTouchAnnotation"}
  ]) {
 }
}

```
```mlir
module {
  firrtl.circuit "Test"  {
    firrtl.module @Test(in %front_port_ahb_0_hmastlock: !firrtl.uint<1> sym @front_port_ahb_0_hmastlock [{class = "Test"}]) {
    }
  }
}
```
